CeWL
Custom wordlist generator from websites

Password Attacks
Description
CeWL is a custom word list generator that spiders a target URL and creates a wordlist from the content. Great for targeted password attacks.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which cewl
Install command:

sudo apt install cewl
Basic Syntax
cewl <url>
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
cewl http://target.com -w wordlist.txt

Generate wordlist	Create custom list	
cewl http://target.com -d 2 -w wordlist.txt

Depth 2 spider	Follow links	
cewl http://target.com -m 6 -w wordlist.txt

Min length 6	Filter short words	
cewl http://target.com -e -w emails.txt

Extract emails	Find emails	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Target a relevant website
2
Run CeWL
3
Review generated wordlist
4
Use with password cracking tools
5
Combine with rules
Understanding the Output
Creates a text file with words scraped from the website.

Important Warnings
